# Midterm — Bio-Inspired AI Audit (Pilot)

**Course:** ITAI 4374 — Neuroscience as a Model for AI Systems
**Instructor:** Professor Patricia McManus
**Student:** Muhammad Umer | Houston City College | Spring 2026

## Overview

This midterm was a pilot neuroscience-based audit of ChatGPT (GPT-4o), evaluating the system against principles from Modules 02, 03, and 04.

## AI System Audited

- System: ChatGPT (GPT-4o) by OpenAI
- Access: chat.openai.com, free tier

## Experiments

- Module 02: Five simultaneous tasks tested sequential vs. parallel processing
- Module 03: Necker Cube and spinning dancer illusion tested perceptual ambiguity
- Module 04: Within-session retention and cross-session memory failure tested

## Key Finding

ChatGPT has no perceptual experience, no cross-session memory, and produces outputs that mimic parallelism through high-speed serial generation — significant divergences from biological intelligence.
